Jumping to and from 2GIS

Artem: By default jumping to 2GIS should be turned off in settings. A user should explicitly choose it if he wants. Logic behind this is that 2GIS is not a global service, and its coverage is small.
issues.title: Add 2GIS maps

issues.body: README and CHANGELOG should reflect all the changes made.
issues.title: Describe changes

issues.body:
Please add Waze LiveMap and Waze Map Editor to the jumping options.

Main URLs:
- Waze LiveMap: https://www.waze.com/livemap
- Waze Map Editor: https://www.waze.com/editor/

Note: The URL can change depending on selected language, for example:
- Spanish Waze LiveMap: https://www.waze.com/es/livemap
- Spanish Waze Map Editor: https://www.waze.com/es/editor/

URL can receive lon, lat, zoom as parameters, for example:
- https://www.waze.com/livemap?lon=-3.70379&lat=40.41678&zoom=15
- https://www.waze.com/editor/?lon=-3.70379&lat=40.41678&zoom=3

Map's permalink can be extracted from the link icon (icon-link) href.

Steps to obtain lon, lat, zoom would be as follows:
1) Get permalink from HTML element ".WazeControlPermalink a.icon-link"
2) Get lon, lat, zoom from permalink
3) Apply zoom correction depending on target mapping service.

Thanks!
issues.title: Jumping from Waze

issues.body:
Now, when clicking on Mapjumper icon, one can jump to 

- Bing Maps
- Google Maps
- MapQuest Open
- OpenStreetMap
- OpenStreetBugs
- Wikimapia
- Yandex Maps

In the extension options make it possible to choose which one to show in the bubble and which one to hide.
issues.title: [Options] Choose mapping providers to jump to and from
